[recv] {"method":"item/completed","params":{"item":{"type":"agentMessage","id":"msg_0765872078f2cda70169cabed606808191a5945bfc72d27503","text":"Created the breakout in [index.circuit.tsx](/workspace/index.circuit.tsx#L54). It uses imported JLC parts for the RP2040, USB-C receptacle, 3.3 V LDO, QSPI flash, 12 MHz crystal, and LED, plus primitive passives and two 20-pin headers for the breakout pins. The board is a 4-layer, USB-powered RP2040 design with CC resistors, USB data series resistors, flash support, crystal load caps, decoupling, RUN/TESTEN biasing, and a GPIO25 LED.\n\nValidation:\n- `tsci check netlist index.circuit.tsx` passes with 0 errors / 0 warnings.\n- `tsci build index.circuit.tsx --ignore-routing-drc` writes [circuit.json](/workspace/dist/index/circuit.json).\n- `tsci snapshot index.circuit.tsx` generated [index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg](/workspace/__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg) and [index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg](/workspace/__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg).\n- The autorouter still hits its iteration limit, so routing is the main remaining weakness even though the design builds and snapshots.\n\n**TSCircuit Developer Feedback**\n- What was confusing or surprising in the tscircuit workflow: JLC search/import behavior was inconsistent. Generic searches often returned nothing, while exact part numbers or LCSC codes worked.\n- What wasted the most time: BOM discovery and repeated autorouter retries. Part search quality and autorouter iteration exhaustion were the biggest time sinks.\n- What docs, APIs, or tooling changes would have helped: clearer docs for JLC search semantics, a way to search/filter by package/category reliably, better guidance for dense RP2040-style layouts, and autorouter controls short of fully disabling routing.\n- Any specific friction points encountered during this run: imported parts can carry odd footprint numeric artifacts, placement output is verbose but not very prescriptive, and snapshot/build succeeded while autorouting still failed, which makes “is this board actually done?” less clear than it should be.","phase":"final_answer","memoryCitation":null},"threadId":"019d3ff0-29e8-70f3-ba1d-de05b9fd0c3e","turnId":"019d3ff0-29ef-7ee2-a576-a7475a31ca5b"}}
